002 x4 h4 y2e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 3:19; 9:7; Acts 13:1; Luke 3:1.) He first married .a </div><div class="t m619 x4 h4 y36f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">daughter of Aretas, King of Arabia Petra a, but after some time </div><div class="t ma8b x4 h4 y2cb ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">he made overtures of marriage to Herodias, the wife of his half-</div><div class="t m17c0 x4 h4 y3e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">brother, Herod Philip I, which she received favorably. Aretas, </div><div class="t m8a2 x4 h4 y394 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">indignant at the insult offered to his daughter, found a pretext </div><div class="t m15a2 x4 h4 yd8c ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for invading the territory of Herod, and• defeated him with </div><div class="t m1835 x4 h4 y205 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">great loss.&quot;</div><div class="t m898 x53 h4a y345 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">—&quot;Smith&apos;s Bible Dictionary.&quot; Art. Herod. </div><div class="t m127 x71 h4 ya71 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m4c6 x73 h4 y384 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The place of John&apos;s imprisonment was the castle of </div><div class="t mb1c x4 h4 y3b7 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Machwrus, a frontier fortress between Perea and Arabia, and </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
